                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": null
                },
                "category": "offensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>When Cratonys damages a creature with her chains, including persistent bleed damage from being impaled by a chain, the creature must succeed at a @Check[type:fortitude|dc:21|traits:disease,virulent] saving throw or contract a severe form of tetanus called velstrac tetanus.</p>\n<hr /><p>Velstracs sometimes intentionally infect their chains with dangerous diseases, such as this aggressive form of tetanus. Tetanus can produce stiffness, muscle spasms strong enough to break bones, and ultimately death.</p>\n<p><strong>Saving Throw</strong> @Check[type:fortitude|dc:21|traits:disease,virulent]</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Onset</strong> [[/br 1d4 #Velstrac Tetanus Onset]]{1d4 days}</p>\n<p><strong>Stage 1</strong> @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Clumsy]{Clumsy 1} (1 week)</p>\n<p><strong>Stage 2</strong> @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Clumsy]{Clumsy 2} and can't speak (1 day)</p>\n<p><strong>Stage 3</strong> @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Paralyzed] (1 day)</p>\n<p><strong>Stage 4</strong> death</p>"
